      "new_latex": "",
      "new_status": "",
      "error_note": "",
      "severity": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "eq_8589",
      "raw": "where tau' = dtau/dt and primes on V denote d/dtau. The Friedmann equation",
      "type": "code",
      "context": "d(tau')/dN = -3*tau' - (1/G_tt)*V'(tau)/H",
      "session": "22d",
      "source_file": "tier0-computation\\s22d_rolling_modulus.py",
      "line": 35,
      "existing_latex": "",
      "audit_status": "none",
      "new_latex": "",
      "new_status": "",
      "error_note": "",
      "severity": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "eq_8590",
      "raw": "We use scale factor a = 1/(1+z) as the independent variable.",
      "type": "code",
      "context": "dtau_dot/dz = [-3*H*tau_dot - V'(tau)/G_tt] / [-(1+z)*H]",
      "session": "22d",
      "source_file": "tier0-computation\\s22d_rolling_modulus.py",
      "line": 44,
      "existing_latex": "",
      "audit_status": "none",
      "new_latex": "",
      "new_status": "",
      "error_note": "",
      "severity": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "eq_8591",
      "raw": "where beta_flux is chosen so V_FR has a minimum at tau_0 = 0.30.",
      "type": "code",
      "context": "For Scenarios A and B, the Freund-Rubin potential is: V_FR(tau) = V_tree(tau) + beta_flux * |omega_3|^2(tau)",
      "session": "22d",
      "source_file": "tier0-computation\\s22d_rolling_modulus.py",
      "line": 50,
      "existing_latex": "",
      "audit_status": "none",
      "new_latex": "",
      "new_status": "",
      "error_note": "",
      "severity": ""
    },
    {
